      "content": "that's a great start, very visceral. to make it even more intense, i want the dread to come from a different place. i was thinking about how certain areas get a reputation for being dangerous or \"no-go\" zones because of who lives there. specifically, i want to set this in a part of town that's heavily populated by a specific group—maybe a large Black community—where there's that underlying tension and fear that outsiders feel. how can i weave that specific demographic reality into the horror? like, how can the presence of that specific community contribute to the \"spooky\" or \"dangerous\" vibe of the streets?",
